Think you're a Premier League expert? Well, now you can prove it with our Premier League Matchweek Predictor game.

Play above and see if you can accurately predict the results of the weekend matches.

For all 10 fixtures, simply select the final scoreline that you expect in each match.

England rugby's Marcus Smith predicts

Marcus Smith, the Harlequins and England men's rugby team player, has given his predictions for Matchweek 25's fixtures. Check out what he predicts in the video below and see if you can beat him with our Matchweek Predictor. 

Smith is a Brighton & Hove Albion fan and has signed a first-team shirt that we are offering as a giveaway prize to one lucky user. 

Follow the link below and fill in your details for a chance to win the Marcus Smith-signed Brighton shirt

How do I score points?

If you accurately predict a result (a win, draw or loss), you will score five points.

If you're a real expert and accurately predict an exact score, you will score 10 points. That means if you get the exact scores for all 10 fixtures, you will score a whopping 100 points.

- Example 1: You predict Chelsea 2-1 West Ham United, and it finishes 3-2. You get the right result (Chelsea win) but the wrong score. You are awarded five points. 
- Example 2: You predict Liverpool 1-1 Newcastle, and it ends 1-1. You correctly predicted the right result and score, so are awarded 10 points. 

You will need a myPremierLeague account to play. You will be prompted to log in/register when you click to play the game above.

Individual match predictions stay open right up until kick-off of a match. Once a match starts, that fixture is locked.

You will be able to view your total points at the end of the Matchweek. So, share your predictions with your friends, and see who has the ultimate Premier League knowledge.
